The issue is that when you try to print an object in JavaScript, using console.log or by using it in a string concatenation, it returns "[object Object]". To fix this, you need to access the individual properties of the object and convert them to a string before returning a result. I will update the function to return the outcome with the highest probability as a string.

```javascript
function PredictCirrhosisOutcomes(N_Days, Drug, Age, Sex, Ascites, Hepatomegaly, Spiders, Edema, Bilirubin, Cholesterol, Albumin, Copper, Alk_Phos, SGOT, Tryglicerides, Platelets, Prothrombin, Stage) {
  // Your prediction code here
  // Calculate probabilities for each outcome (C, CL, D)
  // Return the outcome with the highest probability as a string
  var probabilities = {
    C: 0.5,
    CL: 0.3,
    D: 0.2
  };
  var highestOutcome = Object.keys(probabilities).reduce(function(a, b){ return probabilities[a] > probabilities[b] ? a : b });
  return highestOutcome;
}
```
This updated function will return the outcome with the highest probability as a string, for example "C", "CL", or "D".
